-- 2010-04-27T09:09:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-27/kuwait-supreme-council-may-decide-on-new-refinery-by-year-end-knpc-says.html

          
          
             Kuwait may decide by the end of
this year to build a new refinery, said Bakhit Al-Rashidi,
deputy managing director of planning at Kuwait National
Petroleum Co.  
 The countryâ€™s Supreme Petroleum Council is reviewing the
plan for the refinery, which could start operations by 2015, Al-
Rashidi said in Kuwait City today. Construction tenders may be
issued next year, he said.  
